	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>&#44; <date>November 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Pha</placeName>&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Revd and Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">You will please to forward to <persName>Mr.<lb/> N. Bloom</persName>&#44; care of <persName>E. Bamberger &#38; Bloom</persName>&#44; 3 copies of all the<lb/> religious books used in your Sunday or Sabbath School&#44; or per<lb/>haps in your Educational Society School.  I have established a<lb/> Sabbath School&#44; assisted by <persName>Mrs. N. Bloom</persName>&#59; <persName>Abm Gerstle</persName>&#44; <persName>Louis Dembity</persName> &#38;<lb/> <persName>Dr. H. Filsenheld</persName>&#59; <persName>Mrs. Dembity</persName> and <persName>Miss Sophie Bamberger</persName> also<lb/> offered their kind services&#44; and we desire to have books adapted<lb/> to the capacity and comprehension of pupils from 6 to 15 years.<lb/>  On the two last <date>Sabbaths</date> we had the pleasure to be visited<lb/> by about 250 young ones&#44; all eager to imbibe the lessons<lb/> and truths of our time&#45;honored faith.  The books you send<lb/> will be paid for by return of mail&#44; and we may afterwards<lb/> order a number for each pupil.  If you should possess&#44; or<lb/> could procure&#44; a guide for post&#45;biblical history&#44; adapted for<lb/> scholars of higher classes&#44; or even self&#45;instruction&#44; I would<lb/> be thankful to you&#44; by sending several copies along with<lb/> the others.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You are no doubt aware&#44; that there is a movement<lb/> on hand in my congregation&#44; to engage a Rabbi &#38; Preacher.<lb/>  That it will affect my future to a more or less extent&#44; is sure.<lb/>  There is&#44; how&#45;ever&#44; a majority of members opposed to these procee<lb/>dings&#44; and it will remain a difficult task for the money&#39;d<lb/> minority to accomplish their designs.  They speak of <persName>Dr. Deutsch</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>formerly of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#59; rumors&#44; how&#45;ever&#44; are much<lb/> against him&#44; and&#44; I think&#44; even if he comes here on trial&#44;<lb/> his election will be defeated.  Please to let me know&#44;<lb/> if you choose&#44; how his standing was in your City&#44; and what<lb/> are his religious principles as a Rabbi.  If report speaks<lb/> the truth&#44; my congregation is not yet so much reformed&#44; or<lb/> rather deformed&#44; as to digest a Rabbi with such radical<lb/> views.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please to forward the mentioned books <sic>immediatly</sic>.<lb/>  Hoping and praying that you are well yet and zealous and<lb/> vigorous as ever I subscribe myself</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">most Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">B. H. Gotthelf</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><date>11&#45;9&#45;1862</date></p>
			
